tiny-stats — prior-art attribution
==================================

The SMC (System Management Controller) access protocol used in Sources/CSMC derives from
Apple's open-source PowerManagement `smc.c` and from well-known community ports. These
projects were valuable references for the SMC interface:

- beltex/SMCKit        — https://github.com/beltex/SMCKit        (MIT)
- dkorunic/iSMC        — https://github.com/dkorunic/iSMC        (MIT)

The SMC struct layout and selector constants in Sources/CSMC are the documented kernel
interface; no source files were copied verbatim.

Sensor naming is independent: SMC keys are grouped into components by prefix
(`Sources/SMCKit/SensorClassifier.swift`) and individual sensors are shown by their raw SMC
key; a small set of power-rail labels (`Sources/SMCKit/PowerNames.swift`) is written for this
project. No sensor-name tables are copied from other projects.
